Campus Music DB - MongoDB Educational Project

This project demonstrates a complete migration from spreadsheet-based management 
to a professional MongoDB NoSQL database system for a multi-city music school.

Features:
- Complete MongoDB schema design with validations
- Role-based access control (RBAC) implementation
- Transactional operations for data integrity
- Advanced aggregation pipelines for business analytics
- Comprehensive test dataset with realistic scenarios
- Professional documentation and best practices

Educational Purpose:
This project serves as a comprehensive learning resource for MongoDB concepts,
including document design, validation, aggregation, transactions, and security
implementation in a real-world business context.

For educational and demonstration purposes only.
Not intended for production use without proper review and adaptation.
